Can I start with 1 USD and come back with more than 1 USD?

Instead of asking
"Shortest path?"
We are asking
"Is there any cycle whose multiplication of rates is greater than 1?"

Sol1:
boolean dfs(int start, int curr, double amount) {

    if(curr == start && amount > 1)
        return true;
    visited[curr] = true;
    for(each neighbour){
        if(!visited[neighbour]){
            if(dfs(start,neighbour,amount * exchangeRate))
                return true;
        }
    }
    visited[curr] = false;
    return false;
}

 public static void main(String[] args) {
    for(each currency){
        if(dfs(currency, currency, 1))
            return true;
    }
}

Issue: 100 currencies, DFS explores all possible cycles.number of possible cycles grows exponentially.

Optimisation: Instead of checking every cycle individually,

Convert the multiplication of exchange rates into addition using logarithms.
Convert a profitable cycle (product > 1) into a negative-weight cycle.
Detect the negative cycle in O(V × E) using Bellman-Ford.

public class ArbitrageDetection {

    static class Edge {
        int src, dest;
        double weight;

        Edge(int src, int dest, double rate) {
            this.src = src;
            this.dest = dest;
            // Convert exchange rate to weight
            this.weight = -Math.log(rate);//most imp
        }
    }

    static class Graph {
        int V;
        List<Edge> edges = new ArrayList<>();

        Graph(int V) {
            this.V = V;
        }

        void addEdge(int src, int dest, double rate) {
            edges.add(new Edge(src, dest, rate));
        }

        boolean detectArbitrage() {

            double[] dist = new double[V];
            Arrays.fill(dist, 0);

            // Relax V-1 times
            for (int i = 1; i < V; i++) {
                for (Edge e : edges) {
                    if (dist[e.src] + e.weight < dist[e.dest]) {
                        dist[e.dest] = dist[e.src] + e.weight;
                    }
                }
            }
            // One more relaxation
            for (Edge e : edges) {
                if (dist[e.src] + e.weight < dist[e.dest]) {
                    System.out.println("Arbitrage Opportunity Exists!");
                    return true;
                }
            }
            System.out.println("No Arbitrage Opportunity");
            return false;
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Graph g = new Graph(3);
        // Currency:
        // 0 = USD
        // 1 = EUR
        // 2 = INR
        g.addEdge(0, 1, 0.9);
        g.addEdge(1, 2, 90);
        g.addEdge(2, 0, 0.013);

        g.detectArbitrage();
    }
}
